			<table border="0" cellpadding="12" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
				<TR>
					<td valign="top">
<B CLASS="HeadlineText">FAQ -  Homepage</B><BR><B CLASS="SubHeadlineText">Gear, Stats and effects</B><UL><img SRC="images/icons/arrowbubble.gif" alt="arrow" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13 HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2>&nbsp;<b><A HREF="#1"><u>How high can you stack Vengeance  or ATK effects from worn items?</u></a></b><br><img SRC="images/icons/arrowbubble.gif" alt="arrow" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13 HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2>&nbsp;<b><A HREF="#2"><u>What is the current Flowing Thought Cap?</u></a></b><br><img SRC="images/icons/arrowbubble.gif" alt="arrow" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13 HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2>&nbsp;<b><A HREF="#3"><u>How does Dexterity Affect my Damage?</u></a></b><br><img SRC="images/icons/arrowbubble.gif" alt="arrow" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13 HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2>&nbsp;<b><A HREF="#4"><u>What do I need to do my epic?  Where can I get this item for my epic?  What are some strats involved for my Epic?</u></a></b><br></UL><BR><HR><A NAME="1"><b>Q:&nbsp;How high can you stack Vengeance  or ATK effects from worn items?</b></A><p><b>A:</b>&nbsp;<P>The hard cap for worn item ATK effects is 250 ATK, some prefer to think of this as Vengeance 50.</P>
<P>Any and all ATK effects beyond 250 are wasted. Assuming you have max STR of 305, your max ATK will be 1620 once achieving your effects cap. </P>
<P>Other ATK enhancing effects besides Vengeance are Swift Spirit, Aura of Battle, Timespin, Corporeal Fury, Spiritual Fury, Aura of Bravery, and Aura of Daring to name a few. </P>
<P>Also, Any Avatar effect from either Primal or Ancient Prismatic Weapons is included in this attack cap. Those effects add an additional 100 Attack towards the cap, but like the other forms, do not allow you to exceed it. As an example, if you have 180 unbuffed attack currently, and you proceed to use a Primal or Ancient Prismatic for the effect it will only add 70 points of attack, instead of the full 100.</P><br>
<center><br><a href="#TOP"><img alt="Back to top" BORDER=0 src="Images/icons/TopArrow.gif" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13><br>Top</a></CENTER><HR><A NAME="2"><b>Q:&nbsp;What is the current Flowing Thought Cap?</b></A><p><b>A:</b>&nbsp;<P>Currently the Flowing Thought Cap is 15. This is a cap in all equipment based Unbuffed Mana Regen. This includes such effects as Flowing Thought, Aura of Eternity, Spiritual Fury etc. </P>
<P>This cap does not include any Cast buffs, or right click effects, such as Aura of Eternity, Koadic's Hightened Focus, Voice of Quellious, Spiritual Dominion, nor does the cap affect the AA line, Mental Clarity. You may use the AA and the "Spell Effects" to further bolster your Mana Regen beyond the 15 point cap.</P><br>
<center><br><a href="#TOP"><img alt="Back to top" BORDER=0 src="Images/icons/TopArrow.gif" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13><br>Top</a></CENTER><HR><A NAME="3"><b>Q:&nbsp;How does Dexterity Affect my Damage?</b></A><p><b>A:</b>&nbsp;Currently Dexterity affects several things, it effects the chance of &quot;proccing&quot; a weapon effect, such as Earthcall, Jolting Blades or Cry of Thunder.  It also effects, the chance for scoring a Critical Hit, in normal melee, dependent on if you have the Combat Fury and/or the Fury of the Ages AAs.  Also, this stat effects the chance to score a critical hit with archery.  Adding points to your Dexterity will not directly up your attack, or the damage each of your arrows do, however it will up the chance that any of your arrows may be a Critical Hit, and offer the damage upgrade as such.<br>
<center><br><a href="#TOP"><img alt="Back to top" BORDER=0 src="Images/icons/TopArrow.gif" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13><br>Top</a></CENTER><HR><A NAME="4"><b>Q:&nbsp;What do I need to do my epic?  Where can I get this item for my epic?  What are some strats involved for my Epic?</b></A><p><b>A:</b>&nbsp;All three questions were included in the same topic, as all three are basically the same thing.  The Ranger Epic, while having a few complicated, and/or Rare parts, has been very well defined and recorded over the years.  If you have any questions about it, probably the best place to go for it is www.questing-ranger.com, from there go under the &quot;Resources&quot; catagory, and choose FAQs and Guides, to find probably the most complete walkthrough on the net of the ranger epic.  If that FAQ dosent have the answer you are looking for, there is a good chance the question will have very little impact on your completion of the epic.<br>
